.TH CLITUBE 1 "November 2025" "cliTube 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clitube \- CLI YouTube Player with memorable aliases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clitube
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-video\fR]
.I alias
.br
.B clitube add
.I alias url
.br
.B clitube list
.br
.B clitube remove
.I alias
.br
.B clitube
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR|\fBhelp\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clitube
is a command-line tool for streaming YouTube videos using memorable aliases. It allows you to save YouTube URLs with custom names and quickly play them without remembering full URLs.
.PP
By default, cliTube streams audio-only to save bandwidth. Use the \fB\-v\fR or \fB\-\-video\fR flag to stream both video and audio.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-video
Stream both video and audio. Without this flag, only audio is streamed.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " help
Display help message and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "add " "alias url"
Store a YouTube URL with a custom alias. The alias can be any memorable name.
.TP
.I alias
Play audio from a saved alias. This is the default behavior when no command is specified.
.TP
.B list
Display all saved aliases and their corresponding URLs.
.TP
.BI "remove " alias
.TQ
.BI "rm " alias
Remove an alias from the saved mappings.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a new video alias:
.PP
.nf
.RS
clitube add lofigirl "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jfKfPfyJRdk"
.RE
.fi
.PP
Play audio only (default):
.PP
.nf
.RS
clitube lofigirl
.RE
.fi
.PP
Play with video:
.PP
.nf
.RS
clitube \-v lofigirl
.RE
.fi
.PP
List all saved aliases:
.PP
.nf
.RS
clitube list
.RE
.fi
.PP
Remove an alias:
.PP
.nf
.RS
clitube remove lofigirl
.RE
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/clitube/videos.json
Configuration file storing alias-to-URL mappings in JSON format.
.TP
.I ~/.config/clitube/history.json
Playback history tracking the most recently played videos.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B clitube
requires
.BR mpv (1)
to be installed on the system. mpv is used for streaming audio and video directly from YouTube URLs.
.PP
Install mpv using your package manager:
.PP
.nf
.RS
# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt install mpv

# macOS
brew install mpv

# Arch Linux
sudo pacman \-S mpv
.RE
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (alias not found, mpv not installed, invalid arguments, etc.)
